[3] Diarrhea - Nepal (Humla)
Date: Thu 22 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: HinduOnNet.com [edited]
<http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/holnus/003200407221723.htm>

Diarrhea outbreak claims 27 lives in Nepal
---------------------------------------------
At least 27 people have died, due to an outbreak of diarrhea, in the Humla
district of western Nepal, health officials said.
11 people died in Kalika village, 14 in Maila village, and 2 in Srinagar
village in the district in the last few days, state-run "The Rising Nepal"
reported.
Health workers, with necessary medical equipment, have been dispatched to
control further spread of the disease in the district, the daily paper
said, quoting health officials.
