[5] Cholera - Uganda (Bundibugyo)
Date: Mon 19 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200407190759.html>

Cholera hits Bundibugyo
------------------------
A cholera epidemic has hit the district, with 3 people dead and 10 admitted
to different hospitals. The most affected areas include Rwangara and
Nyahuka sub-counties, and, some parts surrounding Bundibugyo town. The
district director of health services, Dr. Sekyewunda, confirmed the reports
without giving the identities of the dead and the admitted persons.
Sekyewunda said the deceased patients died in Kanara sub-county, and the
remaining patients are hospitalized at Rwangara Health Center in critical
condition. "We have provided drugs to treat the patients," Sekyewunda said.
He called for improved sanitary conditions in the area. Health workers told
The Monitor that other people were admitted at Nyahuka Health Center, near
the Uganda-DR Congo border.
The Vice Chairman LC3 Kanara sub-county, Mr. Ambrose Amumpe Museveni, said
he visited the health center and found the cholera cases being treated
under tree sheds due to over-crowding. He said the measure was a precaution
against infecting other patients.
[Byline: Joseph Kasimbazi]
--
