[6] Cholera - Uganda (Kampala)
Date: Tue 20 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and New Vision (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200407200095.html>

2 residents of Kaseke village, in Naguru Parish II, Nakawa division, were
recently admitted to the Mulago Hospital with cholera. Nakawa resident
district commissioner Samuel Hashaka said that the hardest hit areas were
in Nakawa and Kawempe divisions.
He said cases were cited in Kaseke village, Mbuya II parish, and Luzira
Prison parish, all in Nakawa division.
Hashaka said other areas on high alert were Mulago, Nsoba, Kamokya, and
Kifumbira parish in Kawempe division, where most latrines have been filled
to the brim. He attributed the outbreak to Kampala City Council's laxity to
empty the VIP latrines.
"It's not hygienic to see families continue visiting latrines already
filled to top with maggots moving out. VIP latrines should be emptied
regularly, and this is KCC's job," he said.
[Byline: Fred Ouma]
--
